-# Admin Mobile Dashboard Implementation
-
-## Summary
-
-Updated the admin login flow to display the admin home screen within the `DashboardShell` when users log in on mobile devices, matching the pattern used by other user roles (students, teachers, principals, guardians, tellers).
-
-## What Changed
-
-### Modified File: `lib/auth_gate.dart`
-
-**Added imports:**
-```dart
-import 'admin_vm.dart';
-import 'admin_home.dart';
-```
-
-**Updated admin authentication logic:**
-
-**Before:**
-```dart
-// Admin users go to the admin console
-if (authVm.isAdmin) {
-  debugPrint('AuthGate: user is admin, showing AppRouter');
-  return AppRouter(role: authVm.role!, repo: widget.adminRepo);
-}
-```
-
-**After:**
-```dart
-// Admin users -> AppRouter for web, DashboardShell with AdminHome for mobile
-if (authVm.isAdmin) {
-  debugPrint('AuthGate: user is admin');
-  // Check if using web layout
-  if (useWebLayout(context)) {
-    debugPrint('AuthGate: showing AppRouter (web)');
-    return AppRouter(role: authVm.role!, repo: widget.adminRepo);
-  } else {
-    debugPrint('AuthGate: showing AdminHome in DashboardShell (mobile)');
-    // Mobile: Use DashboardShell with AdminHome
-    final vm = AdminVm(repo: widget.adminRepo);
-    scheduleMicrotask(() => vm.refreshDashboard());
-    return AdminScope(
-      notifier: vm,
-      child: const DashboardShell(
-        center: AdminHome(),
-        welcomeText: '',
-      ),
-    );
-  }
-}
-```
-
-## How It Works
-
-### Desktop/Web (width >= 900px)
-- Uses `AppRouter` with `WebShell`
-- Provides full navigation with routes:
-  - `/admin/home` - Dashboard overview
-  - `/admin/register` - Register new users
-  - `/admin/update` - Update user information
-  - `/admin/report` - View reports
-- Side navigation menu
-- Multi-page experience
-
-### Mobile (width < 900px)
-- Uses `DashboardShell` with `AdminHome`
-- Matches the branded mobile layout used by other roles
-- Single-page dashboard view with metrics
-- Displays:
-  - "Administration Overview" title
-  - Welcome message with admin's name
-  - Metric cards showing:
-    - Active Users count
-    - Schools count
-    - Credit Union Branches count
-    - Student Accounts count
-  - Refresh button to reload metrics
-
-## User Experience
-
-### Mobile Admin Login Flow
-
-1. **User logs in as admin**
-2. **App displays AdminHome in DashboardShell:**
-   - Blue header with LCCU logo
-   - "Administration Overview" title
-   - Welcome message with user's name
-   - Refresh button (top-right)
-   - Grid of metric cards (responsive layout):
-     - 1 column on narrow phones
-     - 2 columns on wider phones
-     - 3-4 columns on tablets
-3. **Each metric card shows:**
-   - Colored icon
-   - Label (e.g., "Active Users")
-   - Count number
-   - White background with blue border
-
-### Desktop/Web Admin Login Flow
-
-1. **User logs in as admin**
-2. **App displays AppRouter with WebShell:**
-   - Side navigation menu with options:
-     - Home
-     - Register
-     - Update
-     - Report
-   - Full routing system
-   - Multiple pages accessible
-
-## Consistency with Other Roles
-
-This change makes admins consistent with ALL other user roles:
-
-| Role | Mobile View | Web View |
-|------|-------------|----------|
-| **Admin** | **DashboardShell + AdminHome** ✅ | **AppRouter + WebShell** |
-| Student | DashboardShell + StudentHome | (same) |
-| Teacher | DashboardShell + TeacherHome | (same) |
-| Principal | DashboardShell + PrincipalHome | (same) |
-| Guardian | DashboardShell + GuardianHome | (same) |
-| Teller | DashboardShell + TellerHome | TellerRouter + WebShell |
-
-## AdminHome Features (Mobile)
-
-### Responsive Metric Cards
-
-The metric cards adapt to screen size:
-- **Card height:** 14-32% of viewport height
-- **Grid columns:**
-  - 1 column: width < 480px
-  - 2 columns: 480px - 720px
-  - 3 columns: 720px - 960px
-  - 4 columns: width > 960px
-- **Icon size:** Scales with card height
-- **Text size:** Scales with card height
-
-### Metrics Displayed
-
-1. **Active Users** (blue icon)
-   - Total count of users in system
-   - Icon: People
-
-2. **Schools** (yellow/orange icon)
-   - Total count of schools
-   - Icon: School building
-
-3. **Credit Union Branches** (green icon)
-   - Total count of credit union locations
-   - Icon: Bank/balance
-
-4. **Student Accounts** (purple icon)
-   - Total count of student savings accounts
-   - Icon: Savings
-
-### Refresh Functionality
-
-- Refresh button in top-right corner
-- Reloads all dashboard metrics
-- Shows loading indicator while refreshing
-- Displays error message if load fails
-
-## Testing
-
-### To Test on Mobile
-
-```bash
-# Run on iOS simulator or Android emulator
-flutter run
-
-# Or run on physical device
-flutter run -d <device-id>
-
-# Log in with admin credentials
-# Verify DashboardShell appears with AdminHome
-# Check that metric cards display correctly
-# Try refresh button
-```
-
-### To Test on Web
-
-```bash
-# Run web version
-flutter run -d chrome
-
-# Resize browser to < 900px width (mobile view)
-# Should show DashboardShell with AdminHome
-
-# Resize browser to >= 900px width (desktop view)
-# Should show AppRouter with WebShell and navigation
-```
-
-### Test Responsive Layout
-
-```bash
-# Test on different screen sizes:
-# - iPhone SE (narrow phone)
-# - iPhone 16 (standard phone)
-# - iPad (tablet)
-
-# Verify metric cards arrange in:
-# - 1 column on narrow screens
-# - 2 columns on medium screens
-# - 3-4 columns on wide screens
-```
-
-## Files Involved
-
-### Modified
-- `lib/auth_gate.dart` - Updated admin authentication routing
-
-### Referenced (no changes needed)
-- `lib/admin_home.dart` - Mobile admin home page
-- `lib/app_router.dart` - Web admin router
-- `lib/admin_vm.dart` - Admin view model
-- `lib/admin_repo.dart` - Admin repository
-- `lib/dashboard_shell.dart` - Mobile dashboard layout
-- `lib/adaptive.dart` - Layout decision logic
-
-## Benefits
-
-1. ✅ **Consistent UX** - ALL roles now use DashboardShell on mobile
-2. ✅ **Branded Mobile Experience** - Admins get the LCCU branded mobile UI
-3. ✅ **Adaptive Layout** - Automatically switches between mobile and web layouts
-4. ✅ **No Breaking Changes** - Web experience unchanged
-5. ✅ **Clean Separation** - Clear distinction between mobile and web code paths
-6. ✅ **Responsive Design** - Metric cards adapt to any screen size
-
-## Navigation on Mobile
-
-**Current behavior (AdminHome only):**
-- Mobile admin view shows only the home dashboard
-- No navigation to other admin pages (register, update, report)
-- This matches the pattern for other roles on mobile
-
-**Future enhancement options:**
-
-1. **Add Bottom Navigation Bar:**
-   ```dart
-   DashboardShell(
-     center: AdminHome(),
-     bottomNavigationBar: AdminBottomNav(), // NEW
-   )
-   ```
-
-2. **Add Floating Action Button:**
-   - FAB could open menu for Register/Update/Report
-
-3. **Add Drawer Navigation:**
-   - Swipe from left to access admin menu
-
-4. **Keep Mobile Simple:**
-   - Mobile = view-only dashboard
-   - Full admin features = web/desktop only
-   - This is the current approach
-
-## Technical Details
-
-### Layout Decision Logic
-
-The `useWebLayout(context)` function from `adaptive.dart`:
-- Returns `false` on native platforms (iOS/Android)
-- Returns `true` on web when width >= 900px
-- Returns `false` on web when width < 900px
-
-This allows web browsers in mobile emulation mode to show the mobile experience.
-
-### View Model Initialization
-
-Admin creates its own scoped VM on mobile:
-```dart
-final vm = AdminVm(repo: widget.adminRepo);
-scheduleMicrotask(() => vm.refreshDashboard());
-return AdminScope(
-  notifier: vm,
-  child: const DashboardShell(...)
-);
-```
-
-This ensures:
-- VM is available to AdminHome via `AdminScope`
-- Dashboard metrics are loaded after first frame
-- Proper cleanup when user logs out
-
-### Metric Loading
-
-1. AdminHome `initState()` calls `vm.refreshDashboard()`
-2. VM fetches data from `AdminRepo`
-3. Metrics populate dashboard cards
-4. User can manually refresh with refresh button
-
-## Next Steps (Optional Enhancements)
-
-Consider these future improvements:
-
-1. **Add Pull-to-Refresh on Mobile**
-   - Wrap content in `RefreshIndicator`
-   - Call `vm.refreshDashboard()` on pull
-
-2. **Add Bottom Navigation for Mobile**
-   - Home, Register, Update, Reports tabs
-   - Similar to web side navigation
-
-3. **Add Action Cards on Mobile**
-   - Quick actions: "Register User", "Generate Report"
-   - Navigate to specific admin functions
-
-4. **Add Search/Filter for Mobile**
-   - Search users, schools, accounts
-   - Filter by status, date, etc.
-
-5. **Keep Mobile Simple (Recommended)**
-   - Mobile = dashboard overview only
-   - Complex admin tasks = use desktop/web
-   - Best for most use cases
-
-## Status
-
-✅ **Complete** - Admin mobile login now displays AdminHome in DashboardShell
-
----
-
-**Date:** November 17, 2025  
-**Changes:** 1 file modified (`lib/auth_gate.dart`)  
-**Testing:** Ready for QA testing  
-**Impact:** All user roles now have consistent mobile experience
