-# 🚨 Quick Fix: "OTP Expired" Error
-
-## Most Likely Causes (in order)
-
-### 1. ⚠️ Redirect URL Not Configured in Supabase
-**This is probably your issue!**
-
-**Fix:**
-1. Go to: https://supabase.com/dashboard
-2. Select project: `juzpizqbhxkncxfpdlxd`
-3. Go to: **Authentication** → **URL Configuration**
-4. Add this EXACT URL under **Redirect URLs**:
-   ```
-   io.supabase.lccu_finx://reset-password
-   ```
-5. Click **Save**
-6. Request a new password reset
-
-### 2. ⏰ Link Actually Expired
-Links expire after **1 hour** for security.
-
-**Fix:**
-- Request a NEW password reset
-- Click the link within 5 minutes
-
-### 3. 🔄 Link Already Used
-Reset links are **one-time use**.
-
-**Fix:**
-- Don't reuse old links
-- Request a NEW link each time
-
-### 4. 📱 Testing on Wrong Device
-Deep links must be clicked on the same device where app is running.
-
-**Fix:**
-- Send yourself the email on test device
-- Or forward email to test device
-- Click link on same device
-
-## Quick Test
-
-```bash
-# 1. Rebuild the app
-flutter clean
-flutter run
-
-# 2. Request password reset
-# 3. Check email IMMEDIATELY
-# 4. Click link within 2 minutes
-# 5. Watch for these logs:
-
-flutter: AuthGate: Session: true    ✅ GOOD
-flutter: AuthGate: Session: false   ❌ BAD (token expired/invalid)
-```
-
-## If Still Not Working
-
-Check `PASSWORD_RESET_TROUBLESHOOTING.md` for detailed debugging steps.
-
-## Expected User Experience
-
-✅ **When it works:**
-1. User clicks "Forgot Password?"
-2. Enters email → sees "Check Your Email"
-3. Opens email, clicks link
-4. App opens to password reset page
-5. Enters new password
-6. Success!
-
-❌ **When token expired:**
-1. User clicks link
-2. App opens to "Link Expired" page
-3. Can request a new link
-
-## Most Common Mistake
-
-**Forgetting to add the redirect URL in Supabase dashboard.**
-
-Double-check this first!
-
----
-
-**Need Help?** See `PASSWORD_RESET_TROUBLESHOOTING.md` for complete guide.
