-
-This app now has a complete password reset flow that allows users to:
-1. Request a password reset from the login screen
-2. Receive an email with a secure reset link
-3. Click the link to open the app and set a new password
-
-## How It Works
-
-### User Flow
-
-1. **User clicks "Forgot Password?"** on the login screen
-2. **Enters their email** on the forgot password page
-3. **Receives an email** from Supabase with a reset link
-4. **Clicks the link** in the email (opens the app via deep link)
-5. **Sets a new password** on the reset password page
-6. **Logs in** with the new password
-
-### Technical Flow
-
-The implementation uses Supabase's built-in password reset functionality:
-
-- `supabase.auth.resetPasswordForEmail()` - Sends the reset email
-- `supabase.auth.updateUser()` - Updates the password after verification
-- Deep linking handles opening the app from the email link
-
-## Files Created/Modified
-
-### New Files
-
-1. **`lib/forgot_password_page.dart`**
-   - Page where users enter their email to request a password reset
-   - Shows success confirmation after email is sent
-
-2. **`lib/reset_password_page.dart`**
-   - Page where users set their new password
-   - Opened automatically when they click the email link
-   - Validates password matches confirmation
-
-### Modified Files
-
-1. **`lib/auth_vm.dart`**
-   - Added `requestPasswordReset()` method
-   - Added `updatePassword()` method
-
-2. **`lib/login_page.dart`**
-   - Added navigation to forgot password page
-   - Imported `forgot_password_page.dart`
-
-3. **`lib/auth_gate.dart`**
-   - Added deep link listener for password recovery
-   - Navigates to reset password page when link is clicked
-
-## Supabase Configuration Required
-
-### 1. Enable Email Auth
-
-In your Supabase dashboard:
-1. Go to **Authentication → Providers**
-2. Ensure **Email** is enabled
-3. Configure **Email Templates** (optional but recommended)
-
-### 2. Configure Redirect URLs
-
-In your Supabase dashboard:
-1. Go to **Authentication → URL Configuration**
-2. Add the following redirect URL:
-   ```
-   io.supabase.lccu_finx://reset-password
-   ```
-
-### 3. Customize Email Template (Optional)
-
-In your Supabase dashboard:
-1. Go to **Authentication → Email Templates**
-2. Select **Reset Password**
-3. Customize the email content as needed
-
-The default template includes:
-```
-{{ .ConfirmationURL }}
-```
-
-This URL will automatically include the deep link that opens your app.
-
-## Deep Link Configuration
-
-### iOS Configuration
-
-Add the following to `ios/Runner/Info.plist`:
-
-```xml
-<key>CFBundleURLTypes</key>
-<array>
-  <dict>
-    <key>CFBundleTypeRole</key>
-    <string>Editor</string>
-    <key>CFBundleURLName</key>
-    <string>io.supabase.lccu_finx</string>
-    <key>CFBundleURLSchemes</key>
-    <array>
-      <string>io.supabase.lccu_finx</string>
-    </array>
-  </dict>
-</array>
-```
-
-### Android Configuration
-
-Add the following to `android/app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml` inside the `<activity>` tag:
-
-```xml
-<intent-filter android:label="flutter_deep_linking">
-  <action android:name="android.intent.action.VIEW" />
-  <category android:name="android.intent.category.DEFAULT" />
-  <category android:name="android.intent.category.BROWSABLE" />
-  <data
-    android:scheme="io.supabase.lccu_finx"
-    android:host="reset-password" />
-</intent-filter>
-```
-
-## Testing the Flow
-
-### Test Password Reset
-
-1. Run the app on a device/simulator
-2. Click **"Forgot Password?"** on the login screen
-3. Enter a valid user email address
-4. Check the email inbox for the reset link
-5. Click the link in the email
-6. The app should open to the reset password page
-7. Enter and confirm a new password
-8. Click **"Update Password"**
-9. Log in with the new password
-
-### Troubleshooting
-
-**Email not received?**
-- Check spam folder
-- Verify email provider in Supabase dashboard
-- Check Supabase logs for errors
-
-**Deep link not working?**
-- Verify redirect URL is configured in Supabase
-- Check iOS/Android manifest configurations
-- Test on a real device (simulators can be unreliable for deep links)
-
-**Password update fails?**
-- Ensure password meets minimum requirements (8 characters)
-- Check Supabase auth settings for password policies
-- Verify user is authenticated (has valid session from email link)
-
-## Key Differences from Manual Password Reset
-
-### Your Original Approach (Manual)
-```typescript
-// Generated random passwords server-side
-const newPassword = generatePassword();
-await supabase.auth.admin.updateUserById(userId, {
-  password: newPassword
-});
-// Then manually sent password to user
-```
-
-**Problems:**
-- Requires admin privileges
-- Less secure (passwords sent in plain text)
-- Manual process for each user
-- No user verification
-
-### New Approach (Built-in)
-```dart
-// User requests reset
-await supabase.auth.resetPasswordForEmail(email);
-// Supabase sends secure link
-// User clicks link and sets own password
-await supabase.auth.updateUser(
-  UserAttributes(password: newPassword)
-);
-```
-
-**Benefits:**
-- ✅ User-initiated and verified
-- ✅ Secure token-based flow
-- ✅ User chooses their own password
-- ✅ No admin intervention needed
-- ✅ Industry-standard pattern
-
-## Security Features
-
-1. **Time-limited tokens**: Reset links expire after a set time
-2. **One-time use**: Each token can only be used once
-3. **Email verification**: Only the email owner can reset the password
-4. **User-chosen passwords**: Users set their own secure passwords
-5. **No plaintext passwords**: Passwords never sent via email
-
