-   - **Important:** Do this on the SAME device where the app is running
-
-5. **Watch debug logs:**
-   ```
-   flutter: AuthGate: Auth event: AuthChangeEvent.passwordRecovery
-   flutter: AuthGate: Session: true/false
-   flutter: ResetPasswordPage: Has active session: true/false
-   ```
-
-### Expected Behavior
-
-**✅ Success:**
-```
-flutter: AuthGate: Auth event: AuthChangeEvent.passwordRecovery
-flutter: AuthGate: Session: true
-flutter: AuthGate: Valid password recovery session, navigating to reset page
-flutter: ResetPasswordPage: Has active session: true
-flutter: ResetPasswordPage: User ID: <user-id>
-```
-
-**❌ Token Expired:**
-```
-flutter: AuthGate: Auth event: AuthChangeEvent.passwordRecovery
-flutter: AuthGate: Session: false
-flutter: AuthGate: Password recovery event but no session
-```
-
-## Common Issues & Solutions
-
-### Issue 1: Link Always Expires Immediately
-
-**Cause:** Redirect URL mismatch
-
-**Solution:**
-1. Check Supabase dashboard redirect URL
-2. Must match EXACTLY: `io.supabase.lccu_finx://reset-password`
-3. Case-sensitive!
-4. No trailing slashes
-
-### Issue 2: Link Opens Browser Instead of App
-
-**Cause:** Deep link not configured properly
-
-**Solution (iOS):**
-```bash
-# Test deep link manually
-xcrun simctl openurl booted "io.supabase.lccu_finx://reset-password"
-```
-
-**Solution (Android):**
-```bash
-# Test deep link manually
-adb shell am start -W -a android.intent.action.VIEW \
-  -d "io.supabase.lccu_finx://reset-password" \
-  com.example.flutterApplication1
-```
-
-### Issue 3: Different Error on Simulator vs Real Device
-
-**Cause:** Deep links behave differently on simulators
-
-**Solution:**
-- Always test on a **real device** for final verification
-- Simulators may not handle deep links consistently
-
-### Issue 4: Link Works First Time, Fails After
-
-**Cause:** Token is one-time use
-
-**Solution:**
-- Request a new link each time
-- Don't reuse old links
-
-### Issue 5: "No Session" Error When Clicking Link
-
-**Cause:** App isn't capturing the deep link token
-
-**Solution:**
-1. Make sure `supabase_flutter` is using PKCE flow:
-   ```dart
-   authOptions: const FlutterAuthClientOptions(
-     authFlowType: AuthFlowType.pkce,
-   ),
-   ```
-2. Verify this is in `lib/supabase_config.dart`
-3. Rebuild: `flutter clean && flutter run`
-
-## Advanced Debugging
-
-### Check Email Template
-
-1. Go to Supabase Dashboard
-2. **Authentication** → **Email Templates**
-3. Select **Reset Password**
-4. Verify the `{{ .ConfirmationURL }}` variable is present
-5. Check the URL format in test emails
-
-### Check Supabase Logs
-
-1. Go to Supabase Dashboard
-2. **Logs** section
-3. Filter by **Auth logs**
-4. Look for reset password requests
-5. Check for any error messages
-
-### Enable Verbose Logging
-
-Add to `lib/main.dart`:
-```dart
-import 'package:flutter/foundation.dart';
-
-void main() async {
-  if (kDebugMode) {
-    // Enable detailed Supabase logging
-    debugPrint('=== SUPABASE DEBUG MODE ===');
-  }
-  // ... rest of main
-}
-```
-
-### Inspect the Email Link
-
-When you receive the email, inspect the URL:
-
-**Should look like:**
-```
-https://juzpizqbhxkncxfpdlxd.supabase.co/auth/v1/verify?
-  token=<long-token>&
-  type=recovery&
-  redirect_to=io.supabase.lccu_finx://reset-password
-```
-
-**Check:**
-- `type=recovery` is present
-- `redirect_to` matches your scheme exactly
-- Token is present
-
-## Testing Checklist
-
-- [ ] Supabase redirect URL is configured correctly
-- [ ] iOS Info.plist has URL scheme
-- [ ] Android Manifest has intent filter
-- [ ] App has been rebuilt after config changes
-- [ ] Testing on a real device (not just simulator)
-- [ ] Requesting fresh link (not reusing old one)
-- [ ] Clicking link within 5 minutes of receiving
-- [ ] Email contains valid reset link
-- [ ] Deep link opens the app (not browser)
-- [ ] Debug logs show `Session: true`
-
-## Token Expiration Settings
-
-To change how long reset links are valid:
-
-1. Go to Supabase Dashboard
-2. **Authentication** → **Settings**
-3. Look for **JWT expiry limit**
-4. Default is 3600 seconds (1 hour)
-
-**Note:** Shorter is more secure, longer is more convenient.
-
-## Alternative: Manual Testing
-
-If automated flow fails, test manually:
-
-```bash
-# 1. Get a reset link from email
-# 2. Extract the token parameter
-# 3. Test deep link directly:
-
-# iOS
-xcrun simctl openurl booted "io.supabase.lccu_finx://reset-password?token=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE&type=recovery"
-
-# Android
-adb shell am start -W -a android.intent.action.VIEW \
-  -d "io.supabase.lccu_finx://reset-password?token=YOUR_TOKEN_HERE&type=recovery" \
-  com.example.flutterApplication1
-```
-
-## Still Not Working?
-
-### Last Resort Steps
-
-1. **Verify package version:**
-   ```yaml
-   # In pubspec.yaml
-   dependencies:
-     supabase_flutter: ^2.0.0  # Should be 2.0.0 or higher
-   ```
-
-2. **Check for package issues:**
-   ```bash
-   flutter pub upgrade
-   flutter clean
-   flutter pub get
-   ```
-
-3. **Try password reset in Supabase Studio:**
-   - Dashboard → Authentication → Users
-   - Find user → Send password recovery email
-   - See if this works differently
-
-4. **Contact support with:**
-   - Supabase project ID
-   - Flutter version (`flutter --version`)
-   - Device/OS being tested
-   - Full error logs
-   - Screenshot of Supabase redirect URL config
-
-## Prevention
-
-### For Future Users
-
-1. **Set reasonable expiration** (1 hour is good)
-2. **Clear error messages** to guide users
-3. **Add rate limiting** to prevent abuse
-4. **Monitor reset requests** in Supabase logs
-5. **Test regularly** on both iOS and Android
-
-## Summary
-
-The "OTP expired" error is almost always caused by:
-
-1. ✅ **Redirect URL mismatch** (most common) - Fix: Verify in Supabase dashboard
-2. ✅ **Actually expired token** - Fix: Request new link
-3. ✅ **Deep link not configured** - Fix: Check platform configs
-4. ✅ **One-time use token reused** - Fix: Request new link
-
-**Quick fix:** Request a fresh password reset link and click it immediately (within 5 minutes) on the same device where the app is running.
