+# Release notes — core branch
+
+Version: 0.1.0 (draft)
+Date: 2025-11-11
+
+Summary
+-------
+This document captures the most recent visible changes made on the `core` branch (features, fixes, and known issues). It is intended for the release manager and QA to validate before publishing.
+
+Highlights
+----------
+- Teller UI: added a combined deposit/withdrawal card with a dropdown to switch modes. Both forms use the selected teacher as the requester.
+- Teacher flows: deposit and withdrawal forms updated to use teacher context; appended transaction notes include the teacher's name where applicable.
+- Validation: deposit form enforces a max amount (submit disabled + validation message) when the amount exceeds the school's available balance.
+- UI polish: buttons updated to use a blue background with bold white text; form validators and field autofill hints added for login pages.
+- Forgot-password: the login page now opens a mailto: to schoolthrift@mylaboriecu.com and shows a confirmation dialog (dialog background set to white).
+- UUIDs: client now generates a proper UUID v4 for RPC calls that require p_request_id (supabase side expects a UUID). This fixes malformed UUID errors.
+- Data handling: several repositories removed use of `updated_at` fields from client projections to reduce errors and noise.
+- Teacher dashboard: the Funds-In-Hand UI is wired to read `teacher_coll.amount` for the logged-in teacher; additional debug logging was added to `TeacherRepo` and `TeacherVm` to aid diagnosis.
+
+Engineering / Packaging
+-----------------------
+- Android package id: a change to the Android `applicationId/namespace` was applied to `com.lccufinx`. Please confirm whether you want this applied across all platforms.
+
+Known issues and follow-ups
+---------------------------
+- Teacher deposit failure: some teacher deposit submissions currently hit a PostgrestException complaining that column `teacher_coll` does not exist. This is likely a DB/view or permissions issue (the `v_tx_enriched` view or related views/functions may reference `teacher_coll`). Action: collect runtime logs (the app now logs teacherId, transaction rows counts, teacher_coll select results) and coordinate with the DB owner to inspect the view definitions and permissions.
+- Analyzer lint: `flutter analyze` reports `include_file_not_found` for `package:flutter_lints/flutter.yaml` in `analysis_options.yaml`. Run `flutter pub get` and ensure the Flutter SDK and packages are in sync. If the project intentionally pins a custom set of lints, adjust the include path.
+- Intl warning: `Intl.v8BreakIterator` deprecation may surface at runtime; resolving this requires a coordinated package/SDK bump and test across platforms.
+- Signing / build: builds that perform release signing will fail if `android/key.properties` is missing or incomplete. Ensure `android/key.properties` with `storeFile`, `storePassword`, `keyAlias`, and `keyPassword` exists on the build machine, or update `android/app/build.gradle.kts` to handle missing properties gracefully.
+
+How to build a release bundle (recommended quick steps)
+-----------------------------------------------------
+1. Ensure dependencies are installed:
+
+```bash
+flutter pub get
+```
+
+2. Verify signing properties are present (if producing a signed release):
+
+Create `android/key.properties` with the following keys (do not commit this file):
+
+```
+storeFile=/absolute/path/to/keystore.jks
+storePassword=your_store_password
+keyAlias=your_key_alias
+keyPassword=your_key_password
+```
+
+3. Build the Android App Bundle:
+
+```bash
+flutter build appbundle --release
+```
+
+What to validate in QA
+----------------------
+- Teacher dashboard displays classes, student counts and transactions for a logged-in teacher.
+- Teller deposit and withdrawal flows succeed for the teacher and include the teacher's name in the note.
+- Max-amount validation prevents exceeding school funds in the deposit flow and surfaces a clear message.
+- Forgot-password triggers an email draft to `schoolthrift@mylaboriecu.com` and confirmation dialog appears.
+- No unexpected analyzer lints block CI (run `flutter analyze` locally).
+
+Next steps / Suggested follow-ups
+--------------------------------
+1. Reproduce the `teacher_coll` PostgrestException using the app logs and share the DB view/function definitions (v_tx_enriched, teacher_coll, related RPCs) with the DB owner.
+2. Decide whether to apply the Android package id change across platforms and update package names (`MainActivity` package, iOS bundle id, macOS, Linux, Windows manifests) accordingly.
+3. Remove tracked IDE files from git (e.g., `*.iml`) so `.gitignore` takes effect. Example:
+
+```bash
+git rm --cached "*.iml"
+git commit -m "chore: remove tracked IDE files so .gitignore can ignore them"
+```
+
+4. Optionally add a short CHANGELOG entry per user-facing release and bump `pubspec.yaml` version before tagging.
+
+Contact
+-------
+For questions about the DB or the RPC contract, contact the backend/DB owner. For Flutter build or CI issues, share `flutter doctor -v` and the full Gradle stacktrace.
+
+-- Release notes generated automatically on 2025-11-11
