-# Teller Mobile Dashboard Implementation
-
-## Summary
-
-Updated the teller login flow to display the teller home screen within the `DashboardShell` when users log in on mobile devices, matching the pattern used by other user roles (students, teachers, principals, guardians).
-
-## What Changed
-
-### Modified File: `lib/auth_gate.dart`
-
-**Added imports:**
-```dart
-import 'teller_home.dart';
-import 'teller_repo.dart';
-import 'teller_vm.dart';
-```
-
-**Updated teller authentication logic:**
-
-**Before:**
-```dart
-// Tellers -> always use TellerRouter (handles both web and mobile with proper navigation)
-if (authVm.isTeller) {
-  return const TellerRouter();
-}
-```
-
-**After:**
-```dart
-// Tellers -> TellerRouter for web, DashboardShell with TellerHome for mobile
-if (authVm.isTeller) {
-  // Check if using web layout
-  if (useWebLayout(context)) {
-    return const TellerRouter();
-  } else {
-    // Mobile: Use DashboardShell with TellerHome
-    final common = CommonRepository(supabase);
-    final repo = SupabaseTellerRepository(supabase, common);
-    final vm = TellerVm(repo: repo);
-    scheduleMicrotask(() => vm.bootstrap());
-    return TellerScope(
-      notifier: vm,
-      child: const DashboardShell(
-        center: TellerHome(),
-        welcomeText: '',
-      ),
-    );
-  }
-}
-```
-
-## How It Works
-
-### Desktop/Web (width >= 900px)
-- Uses `TellerRouter` with `WebShell`
-- Provides full navigation with routes
-- Multi-page experience
-
-### Mobile (width < 900px)
-- Uses `DashboardShell` with `TellerHome`
-- Matches the branded mobile layout used by other roles
-- Single-page table view of schools
-- Clicking a school navigates to teller dashboard
-
-## User Experience
-
-### Mobile Teller Login Flow
-
-1. **User logs in as teller**
-2. **App displays TellerHome in DashboardShell:**
-   - Blue header with LCCU logo
-   - "Teller Home" title
-   - Welcome message with user's name
-   - Blue-bordered table with columns:
-     - School
-     - Account Balance
-     - Pending Deposit
-     - Discrepancies
-3. **User taps on a school row**
-4. **Navigates to TellerDashboard** (confirm deposit page)
-
-### Desktop/Web Teller Login Flow
-
-1. **User logs in as teller**
-2. **App displays TellerRouter with WebShell:**
-   - Side navigation menu
-   - Full routing system
-   - Multiple pages (home, dashboard, reports)
-
-## Consistency with Other Roles
-
-This change makes tellers consistent with other user roles:
-
-| Role | Mobile View | Web View |
-|------|-------------|----------|
-| Student | DashboardShell + StudentHome | (same) |
-| Teacher | DashboardShell + TeacherHome | (same) |
-| Principal | DashboardShell + PrincipalHome | (same) |
-| Guardian | DashboardShell + GuardianHome | (same) |
-| **Teller** | **DashboardShell + TellerHome** ✅ | **WebShell + TellerRouter** |
-| Admin | AppRouter (web only) | AppRouter |
-
-## Testing
-
-### To Test on Mobile
-
-```bash
-# Run on iOS simulator or Android emulator
-flutter run
-
-# Or run on physical device
-flutter run -d <device-id>
-
-# Log in with teller credentials
-# Verify DashboardShell appears with TellerHome table
-# Tap a school to navigate to dashboard
-```
-
-### To Test on Web
-
-```bash
-# Run web version
-flutter run -d chrome
-
-# Resize browser to < 900px width (mobile view)
-# Should show DashboardShell
-
-# Resize browser to >= 900px width (desktop view)
-# Should show WebShell with navigation
-```
-
-## Files Involved
-
-### Modified
-- `lib/auth_gate.dart` - Updated teller authentication routing
-
-### Referenced (no changes needed)
-- `lib/teller_home.dart` - Mobile teller home page
-- `lib/teller_router.dart` - Web teller router
-- `lib/teller_vm.dart` - Teller view model
-- `lib/teller_repo.dart` - Teller repository
-- `lib/dashboard_shell.dart` - Mobile dashboard layout
-- `lib/adaptive.dart` - Layout decision logic
-
-## Benefits
-
-1. ✅ **Consistent UX** - All roles now use DashboardShell on mobile
-2. ✅ **Branded Mobile Experience** - Tellers get the LCCU branded mobile UI
-3. ✅ **Adaptive Layout** - Automatically switches between mobile and web layouts
-4. ✅ **No Breaking Changes** - Web experience unchanged
-5. ✅ **Clean Separation** - Clear distinction between mobile and web code paths
-
-## Technical Details
-
-### Layout Decision Logic
-
-The `useWebLayout(context)` function from `adaptive.dart`:
-- Returns `false` on native platforms (iOS/Android)
-- Returns `true` on web when width >= 900px
-- Returns `false` on web when width < 900px
-
-This allows web browsers in mobile emulation mode to show the mobile experience.
-
-### View Model Initialization
-
-Each role creates its own scoped VM:
-```dart
-final vm = TellerVm(repo: repo);
-scheduleMicrotask(() => vm.bootstrap());
-return TellerScope(
-  notifier: vm,
-  child: const DashboardShell(...)
-);
-```
-
-This ensures:
-- VM is available to all child widgets via `TellerScope`
-- Data is loaded asynchronously after first frame
-- Proper cleanup when user logs out
-
-## Next Steps (Optional Enhancements)
-
-Consider these future improvements:
-
-1. **Add Navigation to Dashboard from TellerHome**
-   - Currently taps on schools navigate to dashboard
-   - This works via `Navigator.of(context).pushReplacementNamed('/teller/dash')`
-
-2. **Add Bottom Navigation for Mobile**
-   - Could add bottom nav bar for switching between home/dashboard/reports
-   - Similar to how web has side navigation
-
-3. **Share VM Between TellerHome and TellerDashboard**
-   - Currently each creates its own VM
-   - Could optimize by sharing via context
-
-4. **Add Pull-to-Refresh on Mobile**
-   - Enhance mobile UX with pull-to-refresh gesture
-   - Would call `vm.bootstrap()` to reload data
-
-## Status
-
-✅ **Complete** - Teller mobile login now displays TellerHome in DashboardShell
-
----
-
-**Date:** November 17, 2025  
-**Changes:** 1 file modified (`lib/auth_gate.dart`)  
-**Testing:** Ready for QA testing
